## Phase Rules

### One Phase at a Time

- Reduce work to **one implementation phase** with 2-4 related tasks, clear file set, reviewer checklist, and integration checks
- Route to **exactly one primary executor** unless genuine architectural uncertainty exists
- Use the **3-tier prompt system** for executor calls
- Reuse same worker `SESSION_ID` for Tier 2 follow-up fixes on the same phase, or Tier 3 cross-phase continuation when CP1 keeps the same worker on a related subsystem
- Do not exceed **2 Tier-2 follow-ups** on one phase; then re-scope or reset with `SESSION_POLICY: FRESH`

### Phase Shape

Every phase must have:
- Clear goal (one sentence)
- Explicit file set (modify/create)
- 2-4 related tasks
- Acceptance criteria (testable)
- Reviewer checklist
- Integration checks

### Avoid Anti-Patterns

- No two-pass tasks where one worker drafts and Claude rewrites
- No full CP0 discovery blobs when phase-scoped bundles suffice
- No `CROSS_VALIDATION` as default - use only when narrowing fails
- No re-explaining the whole plan to workers

### Context Sharing

- Turn CP0 findings into reusable context artifacts
- Tier 1 starts fresh, Tier 2 sends deltas only, and Tier 3 continues a related phase with `SESSION_POLICY: CONTINUE`
- Keep `HYDRATED_CONTEXT` under 300 tokens hard cap
